🎯 My Implementation Approach
I'll build a webhook-driven subscription system that connects your landing page's Stripe payments to Guide's access control. Here's how it will work:

The Flow:
Landing Page → User chooses monthly ($12) or annual ($144) → pays via Stripe → email captured
Stripe Webhook → Fires to your landing page → stores subscription in shared PostgreSQL database
Guide Signup → User creates account → we verify their email has active subscription → allow ONE account creation
Guide Login → Every session checks subscription status → blocks access if expired/cancelled
Prevention System → One subscription email = one Guide account (enforced at database level)
What I'll Build:
For Guide (this app):

✅ New subscriptions table in your existing PostgreSQL database
✅ Subscription verification middleware (checks on login + session)
✅ Modified signup flow (requires active subscription)
✅ One-account-per-email enforcement
✅ Friendly error messages with links back to landing page
✅ Optional: Admin dashboard to view/manage subscriptions
For Your Landing Page (blueprint/documentation):

✅ Webhook endpoint code (Node.js/Python) to receive Stripe events
✅ Signature verification for security
✅ Event handlers for: subscription.created, invoice.paid, subscription.deleted
✅ Database connection setup (reuse Guide's PostgreSQL)
✅ Environment variables guide (Stripe keys, database URL)
Security Features:

✅ Signed webhook verification (prevents fake requests)
✅ Email-based linking (prevents multiple accounts)
✅ Status checks with caching (performance + real-time)
✅ Grace period for failed payments (1-2 days)
